---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Use — PlainHireCheck"
  description="Terms of use for PlainHireCheck. Information about acceptable use, disclaimers, and limitations of liability."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Terms of Use' }]}
>
  <section class="py-8 md:py-12">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)] mb-6">Terms of Use</h1>
      <div class="prose max-w-none text-[var(--color-muted)] [&_h2]:text-[var(--color-foreground)] [&_strong]:text-[var(--color-foreground)]">
        <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> January 15, 2026</p>

        <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing and using PlainHireCheck ("plainhirecheck.com"), you agree to these Terms of Use.
          If you do not agree, please do not use this site.
        </p>

        <h2>Information Purpose</h2>
        <p>
          PlainHireCheck is an informational resource that presents publicly available state contractor licensing data
          in a more accessible format. The information on this site is provided for general informational purposes only
          and should not be relied upon as legal, professional, or contractor verification advice.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Always verify contractor credentials directly with your state's licensing board before hiring.</strong>
          Licensing requirements change and our data, while regularly updated, may not reflect the most current state.
        </p>

        <h2>Accuracy and Completeness</h2>
        <p>
          While we strive to present accurate information, we make no warranties about the completeness,
          reliability, or accuracy of the data. State licensing requirements change with legislation —
          always verify important information directly with official state licensing boards.
        </p>

        <h2>No Professional Advice</h2>
        <p>
          Nothing on this site constitutes legal, professional, or contractor recommendation advice of any kind.
          Any decisions you make based on information found here are solely your responsibility.
        </p>

        <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The underlying government data presented on this site is in the public domain. Our original
          design, code, text, and organization of the data are copyrighted by Kiznis.Studio. You may
          not scrape, reproduce, or redistribute our site design or original content without permission.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          This site contains links to state licensing board websites and other third-party resources.
          We are not responsible for the content, accuracy, or availability of those sites.
        </p>

        <h2>Advertising</h2>
        <p>
          This site displays advertisements through Google AdSense to support its operation.
          Ads are served by third parties and are subject to their own terms and privacy policies.
        </p>

        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, PlainHireCheck and Kiznis.Studio shall not be liable
          for any damages arising from your use of or inability to use this site, or any reliance on
          the data presented herein.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms at any time. Continued use of the site constitutes acceptance of any changes.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these terms? Email <a href="mailto:hello@plainhirecheck.com">hello@plainhirecheck.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
